  "description": [
    "PAGE TEN insearch _ of GOOD E XTING by RUTH ANN of NEWINGTON This week we have a request that I particular ly liked answering Dear Ruth Ann I love to bake muffins and biscuits and I think I have tried every varia tion but perhaps you have a new one for me Here is a bran type muf fin that is dark and moist having a texture similar to brown bread In fact they go well with a baked bean supper they are also naturals for a hearty breakfast RAISIN BRAN MUFFINS 2 C All Bran 12 C Molasses 1 14 C milk 1 Egg 1 C sifted flour 1 Tsp baking soda 12 Tsp salt 12 C raisins or currants Combine all bran mol asses and milk let stand until most of moisture is taken up Add egg and beat well Sift together flour soda and salt add with raisins or currants to bran mis ture stirring only until combined Fill greased muffin pan 34 full Bake in moderately hot oven 400 Deg F about 25 minutes Let stand a bout 5 minutes before re moving from pans Yield 12 muffins CREATIVE SERVICES THE TOWNCRIER Shell Heating Oil"
  ],
